edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.router
Class StaticSourceHandler

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.router.StaticSourceHandler

public class StaticSourceHandler
extends java.lang.Object

This class separates the static nets in to separate nets so they can be routed more easily by the router. This same process happens in Xilinx PAR during the routing phase.

Author:
Chris Lavin Created on: Jun 10, 2010

getPinsNeedingNonTIEOFFSource

public static java.util.HashSet<java.lang.Integer> getPinsNeedingNonTIEOFFSource(java.lang.String partName,
                                                                                 WireEnumerator we)
This method generates a set of wires in a particular part switch box that require a SLICE to supply the static source. This is true of CLB_B wires in Virtex 4.

Parameters:
partName - Name of the part to generate the set for.
we - The wire enumerator corresponding to the supplied part.
Returns:
The set of all switch matrix wires that require a SLICE to supply a static source.
